    "Tony W. Cartledge": ")\nDavid `[char_David_Rut_4]` said the king of Israel had come out to hunt him like a\nsingle flea, like one who hunts a partridge in the mountains. (\nv. 21). David `[char_David_Rut_4]` said, \u201cThe LORD\nrewards everyone for his righteousness and his faithfulness\u201d\n(\nv. 21), much as Jonathan\nhad done previously (20:14-16). As he had done for Jonathan\n(20:17), David `[char_David_Rut_4]` swore to protect Saul\u2019s descendants ("
